    {
      "text": "Cho Aniki (超兄貴, Chō Aniki; lit. \"Super Big Brother\") is a 1992 side-scrolling shooter video game developed by Masaya Games and published by Nippon Computer Systems (NCS). The first game in the Cho Aniki series, it was originally released in 1992 on the PC Engine Super CD-ROM² System add-on. Many years later, the game was released as part of Project EGG for Microsoft Windows only in Japan, the Wii Virtual Console and the PC Engine/TurboGrafx-16 Mini worldwide, making it the first time this game has seen the release in Western regions. Cho Aniki was also included with the sequel Ai Cho Aniki as part of Cho Aniki Collection for the Nintendo Switch, which was first released in Japan on December 12, 2024 and then in North America and Europe on January 29, 2025.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
